## What to Do Next

**1. Read the blog post**

Get a deeper walkthrough of the Coding Agent Explorer and the ideas from the talk:
[Introducing the Coding Agent Explorer (.NET)](https://nestenius.se/ai/introducing-the-coding-agent-explorer-net/)

**2. Download and explore it yourself**

The Coding Agent Explorer is a hands-on .NET project that lets you explore how a coding agent works from the inside. Clone it, run it, and break it apart:
[github.com/tndata/CodingAgentExplorer](https://github.com/tndata/CodingAgentExplorer)

**3. Connect with me on LinkedIn**

I post regularly about .NET, Azure, and web security. Feel free to connect:
[linkedin.com/in/torenestenius](https://www.linkedin.com/in/torenestenius/)

**4. Interested in a talk or training at your company?**

I offer workshops and training on .NET, Azure, authentication, and AI topics. If you want to bring this (or another topic) to your team or event, feel free to [get in touch](https://tn-data.se/contact/)!


